          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a kind of instruction manual to be used by a priest or religious practitioner engaged in the worship (pūjā) of earthen (pārthiva) liṅgas, emblems of the Hindu god Śiva in order to remove sins and receive other worldly benefits. Text is from a larger work called the Pārthivacintāmaṇi.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Pārthivanirṇayapūjana</title>
              <title type="vernacular">पार्थिवनिर्णयपूजन</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>scribe</resp>
                <persName type="authority">Lohanī, Viṣṇudatta</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīpārthivacintāmaṇau pārthivanirṇayaṃ pūjanaṃ ca samāptaṃ śubham samvat 1901 māse 1 pakṣe 2 tithau harivodhanī 11 vāre 4 etac chubhadine likhitaṃ graṃthaṃ lohanīviṣṇudattena svārthaṃ parārthaṃ vātatsat śrīgaurīśaṅkarābhyān namaḥ śrīrāmaḥ śubhaṃ sarveṣām (f. 14r).</colophon>
            </msItem>
